WEBVTT

00:04.352 --> 00:06.049
<i>- In the criminal justice
system,</i>

00:06.093 --> 00:07.442
<i>sexually based offenses</i>

00:07.485 --> 00:09.618
<i>are considered
especially heinous.</i>

00:09.661 --> 00:12.186
<i>In New York City,
the dedicated detectives</i>

00:12.229 --> 00:14.014
<i>who investigate
these vicious felonies</i>

00:14.057 --> 00:15.450
<i>are members of an elite squad</i>

00:15.493 --> 00:17.321
<i>known as
the Special Victims Unit.</i>

00:17.365 --> 00:19.019
<i>These are their stories.</i>

00:19.062 --> 00:20.542
<i>[dramatic sting]</i>

00:20.585 --> 00:23.153
- Your husband, Leon,
is getting paroled tomorrow.

00:23.197 --> 00:24.502
<i>♪</i>

00:24.546 --> 00:27.070
- If Leon came back,
you could be in a grave.

00:27.114 --> 00:29.942
And that little boy
would be alone.

00:29.986 --> 00:31.727
- Sergeant Fin.
- Andre.

00:31.770 --> 00:33.381
- Think fast.

00:33.424 --> 00:36.036
<i>- My man, if you're ever
scared about anything,</i>

00:36.079 --> 00:37.820
<i>call me.</i>

00:37.863 --> 00:39.082
Andre.

00:39.126 --> 00:40.127
Slow down.

00:40.170 --> 00:41.737
<i>[dramatic sting]</i>

00:41.780 --> 00:44.348
- You didn't know your husband,
Leon, was getting paroled?

00:44.392 --> 00:46.350
- Not until Sergeant Tutuola
told me.

00:46.394 --> 00:47.786
- And that's
when you let him know

00:47.830 --> 00:50.702
Leon was reaching out to you
through your son, Andre?

00:50.746 --> 00:52.008
- Probably.

00:52.052 --> 00:53.183
- And isn't that
when you asked him

00:53.227 --> 00:55.185
not to report it
to Leon's parole officer?

00:55.229 --> 00:57.144
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

00:57.187 --> 00:59.276
- What I remember--

00:59.320 --> 01:01.757
Mr. Tutuola told me
it was a violation.

01:01.800 --> 01:04.238
He'd have to report it and
Leon would go back to prison.

01:04.281 --> 01:06.631
- Mrs. Fuller,
are you saying under oath

01:06.675 --> 01:08.503
that you never asked
Sergeant Tutuola

01:08.546 --> 01:10.418
to refrain from going
to Leon's PO?

01:10.461 --> 01:12.202
- Counselor, the law is clear.

01:12.246 --> 01:14.378
Sergeant Tutuola
was obligated to report.

01:14.422 --> 01:17.120
- Isn't it true you wanted
Leon out on parole?

01:17.164 --> 01:18.817
So he'd have
to pay child support?

01:18.861 --> 01:20.297
- [scoffs]

01:20.341 --> 01:22.604
What I-I didn't want...

01:24.432 --> 01:28.088
I didn't want my son

01:28.131 --> 01:29.785
to watch his father get shot

01:29.828 --> 01:32.222
and bleed out
on the kitchen floor.

01:33.876 --> 01:34.920
- Come on, Leon.
Stop.

01:34.964 --> 01:36.618
[indistinct chatter]
- Don't do it!

01:36.661 --> 01:37.967
Come on.
[gunshot]

01:38.010 --> 01:39.969
[all yelping]
- [cries]

01:40.012 --> 01:42.754
<i>[tense music]</i>

01:42.798 --> 01:48.934
<i>♪</i>

01:48.978 --> 01:51.981
[grunting]

01:52.024 --> 01:54.462
[both breathing heavily]

01:54.505 --> 01:56.594
- Hoo!

01:58.683 --> 02:00.598
[panting]

02:00.642 --> 02:01.947
[inhales]

02:01.991 --> 02:03.601
[exhales]

02:03.645 --> 02:05.429
Well, I-I've been
thinking about that

02:05.473 --> 02:08.040
since the Mason-Dixon Line,
darling.

02:08.084 --> 02:10.695
- [sighs]

02:10.739 --> 02:13.350
- What?

02:13.394 --> 02:15.178
- Just wish you
would've called, Dwight.

02:15.222 --> 02:16.658
Before just showing up?

02:16.701 --> 02:18.442
- Oh, here we go.

02:18.486 --> 02:20.662
I drive 16 hours straight

02:20.705 --> 02:22.403
with a case
of Popov under my arm,

02:22.446 --> 02:24.274
a princess gown
for my daughter.

02:24.318 --> 02:27.190
- No.
No, that was--that was sweet.

02:28.191 --> 02:31.890
Maybe next time you could
bring something for Will too?

02:31.934 --> 02:33.631
- He ain't my kid.

02:33.675 --> 02:34.676
[door opens]

02:34.719 --> 02:36.982
- Mom?

02:37.026 --> 02:38.332
I'm hungry.

02:38.375 --> 02:39.681
- I'll be right out, sweetie.

02:39.724 --> 02:41.204
- I'll put the fruit tarts
in the toaster, Ma.

02:41.248 --> 02:42.336
- The hell are you doing?

02:42.379 --> 02:44.164
Shut the damn door.

02:45.904 --> 02:47.384
Kid's a fruit tart himself.

02:47.428 --> 02:50.170
- Leave him alone.

02:50.213 --> 02:51.475
Hey.

02:51.519 --> 02:54.826
How about I make us
some bacon and eggs?

02:54.870 --> 02:56.567
- You know what?
We should get married.

02:56.611 --> 02:59.440
The way you bust my balls,
might as well be my wife.

02:59.483 --> 03:02.399
- [laughs]
Was that a proposal?

03:02.443 --> 03:05.359
<i>[soft uneasy music]</i>

03:05.402 --> 03:08.057
<i>♪</i>

03:08.100 --> 03:10.015
[eggs sizzling]

03:10.059 --> 03:11.495
- More?
- Ow!

03:11.539 --> 03:13.628
- You little thief.
- Guys, what's going on?

03:13.671 --> 03:15.282
- He ate all my damn bacon.

03:15.325 --> 03:17.371
- I don't even eat bacon.
I'm a vegan.

03:17.414 --> 03:19.547
- Well, your kid's a liar
and a cry baby.

03:19.590 --> 03:21.201
- Ow!

03:21.244 --> 03:22.680
I'm not crying.

03:22.724 --> 03:24.943
- Just let him go.
I'll make more.

03:26.945 --> 03:29.252
- Boy, you don't toughen up,

03:29.296 --> 03:30.732
this world will run
right over you.

03:30.775 --> 03:33.909
- Dwight!
How 'bout some more coffee?

03:35.476 --> 03:37.913
- It's about time.

03:39.262 --> 03:41.046
Well, how about you?
You want some?

03:41.090 --> 03:42.265
- I don't drink coffee, Daddy.

03:42.309 --> 03:43.875
- Oh, you don't.

03:43.919 --> 03:45.703
Since when?

03:45.747 --> 03:50.360
<i>♪</i>

03:50.404 --> 03:52.623
- I'm so sorry.
Hang in there, Fin.

03:52.667 --> 03:55.104
- What--five hours
and they're still deposing him?

03:55.147 --> 03:56.540
This is not right.

03:56.584 --> 03:58.716
He saves Andre's life
and Joelle sues him?

03:58.760 --> 04:00.805
- She's in a long-term
abusive relationship.

04:00.849 --> 04:02.024
She's identifying
with her abuser.

04:02.067 --> 04:03.286
- Um, yeah, I know.

04:03.330 --> 04:06.768
But Fin is the last man
who deserves this.

04:06.811 --> 04:09.031
- Hey, is it okay if I take
a run up to Fort George?

04:09.074 --> 04:10.075
- Do you wanna tell me why?

04:10.119 --> 04:11.642
- A nurse called from I.S. 196.

04:11.686 --> 04:13.427
A boy came in with bruising.

04:13.470 --> 04:16.125
- What'd the kid tell her?
- He was evasive.

04:16.168 --> 04:18.649
She killed the mom and
overheard a domestic situation.

04:18.693 --> 04:20.738
- Okay, a DV should go
to the local precinct.

04:20.782 --> 04:22.566
- There's a daughter
in the apartment.

04:22.610 --> 04:25.874
The nurse is worried
about sexual abuse.

04:25.917 --> 04:27.789
- Okay.
Uh, Rollins, go with.

04:27.832 --> 04:30.574
And if it sounds
like a situation,

04:30.618 --> 04:33.316
then you wait for backup.

04:37.538 --> 04:39.235
- Ugh, she still has me
on a short leash.

04:39.279 --> 04:40.758
- It's not you.

04:40.802 --> 04:43.195
Four years ago,
we lost a good man

04:43.239 --> 04:45.894
on a DV call.

04:45.937 --> 04:47.417
Chief Dodds's son.

04:47.461 --> 04:50.246
She's never forgiven herself.

04:50.290 --> 04:53.249
<i>[somber music]</i>

04:53.293 --> 04:56.470
<i>♪</i>

04:56.513 --> 04:59.299
[knocking]
- NYPD, open up please.

04:59.342 --> 05:01.779
- She's home.

05:01.823 --> 05:03.999
I saw that jerk
leave without her.

05:04.042 --> 05:05.435
- Go ahead.

05:05.479 --> 05:08.090
What--what jerk?

05:08.133 --> 05:10.440
- Look...
[keys jangling]

05:10.484 --> 05:13.400
Leave me out of this.

05:13.443 --> 05:16.403
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

05:16.446 --> 05:18.405
- I got her.

05:18.448 --> 05:23.192
♪

05:23.235 --> 05:24.628
- All clear.
Place is empty.

05:24.672 --> 05:26.326
- I got a pulse.
Call it in.

05:26.369 --> 05:28.328
- SVU Portable to Central,

05:28.371 --> 05:30.112
we need a bus
to 71 Naval Avenue

05:30.155 --> 05:32.332
for unconscious female
hit in the head...

05:33.550 --> 05:36.510
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

05:36.553 --> 05:43.691
<i>♪</i>

06:20.292 --> 06:23.557
<i>-</i>Irena Nowak.
Her son, Will, is from her ex.

06:23.600 --> 06:25.080
And she's got a six-year-old

06:25.123 --> 06:26.864
with her trucker boyfriend,
Dwight Wagner.

06:26.908 --> 06:28.518
- He's a good old boy.
He came in all hopped up.

06:28.562 --> 06:29.998
I sent him downstairs to vape.

06:30.041 --> 06:31.695
- What about the kids?
- The school's holding them.

06:31.739 --> 06:33.349
- Okay.
Good.

06:33.393 --> 06:35.438
Kat, see if you can get
any more out of Will.

06:35.482 --> 06:38.789
Rollins, you take Dwight.

06:38.833 --> 06:42.053
So you don't
remember everything

06:42.097 --> 06:45.317
but you think
that you fainted?

06:45.361 --> 06:47.015
- I was rushing
to pick up the kids.

06:47.058 --> 06:48.756
- Mm-hmm.

06:48.799 --> 06:50.540
So, Irena, you have a--

06:50.584 --> 06:52.890
you have a black eye

06:52.934 --> 06:56.633
and some bruising on your arm.

06:57.852 --> 07:00.245
- Uh, I'm supposed
to be on the road already.

07:00.289 --> 07:02.117
I do long hauls
for a freight broker.

07:02.160 --> 07:04.293
But Irena called,
so I came right away.

07:04.336 --> 07:05.599
- So you and she
don't live together?

07:05.642 --> 07:07.122
- No, I live in West Virginia.

07:07.165 --> 07:09.777
Irena and I, we see each other
when I pass through.

07:09.820 --> 07:11.822
- Were you two in a fight
before you left?

07:11.866 --> 07:13.781
We got a call
that there was a disturbance.

07:13.824 --> 07:15.565
- People here need
to mind their business.

07:15.609 --> 07:16.653
- Oh.

07:16.697 --> 07:18.133
- You know back home,

07:18.176 --> 07:21.745
it's legal to beat your wife
on Sunday.

07:21.789 --> 07:24.966
You can look that up.

07:25.009 --> 07:26.576
- We weren't fighting.

07:26.620 --> 07:29.013
- Okay.

07:29.057 --> 07:30.972
Do you remember getting a call

07:31.015 --> 07:33.148
from Will's school?

07:33.191 --> 07:35.106
- Will, how is he?
Where is he?

07:35.150 --> 07:37.152
- Well, the school nurse
called and said

07:37.195 --> 07:40.329
that Will also had bruising
on his arm.

07:40.372 --> 07:42.374
Do you know anything
about that?

07:42.418 --> 07:44.202
- These schools overreact.

07:44.246 --> 07:45.639
Boys tussle.

07:45.682 --> 07:47.249
- So do you know
how it happened?

07:47.292 --> 07:48.859
- Well, I can guess.

07:48.903 --> 07:49.991
Willy's a runt.

07:50.034 --> 07:51.296
The other kids push him around.

07:51.340 --> 07:53.342
I try to teach him
how to fend for himself.

07:53.385 --> 07:55.736
- Teach him how?

07:55.779 --> 07:57.172
<i>[tense music]</i>

07:57.215 --> 07:59.217
- Look.
I know what you're getting at.

07:59.261 --> 08:02.046
But hand to God,
I've never hurt that boy.

08:04.135 --> 08:06.137
- I fell.

08:06.181 --> 08:07.530
Anyway, it doesn't matter.

08:07.574 --> 08:10.533
Dwight'll be gone soon.

08:10.577 --> 08:12.622
My kids--I-I need--
I need to get my kids.

08:12.666 --> 08:14.755
- No, no,
your kids are at school

08:14.798 --> 08:17.888
with a detective.

08:17.932 --> 08:19.977
<i>♪</i>

08:20.021 --> 08:21.936
- I'm a good mother.

08:21.979 --> 08:24.416
I would never let anything
happen to either of them.

08:29.073 --> 08:30.466
<i>- Will always has a story.</i>

08:30.510 --> 08:33.600
He fell off the monkey bars.
He tripped.

08:33.643 --> 08:35.166
- And you didn't believe him?

08:35.210 --> 08:36.516
- Not today.

08:36.559 --> 08:39.431
After I called his mother,
I tried his father.

08:39.475 --> 08:42.957
He said Irena's boyfriend
bullies Will.

08:43.000 --> 08:44.872
I should have called before.

08:44.915 --> 08:46.526
- So this has been going on
for a while?

08:46.569 --> 08:48.397
- Worse now with the pandemic.

08:48.440 --> 08:49.746
Not just him.

08:49.790 --> 08:52.488
Lots of these kids
stuck at home, stressed,

08:52.532 --> 08:53.924
no one to look out for them

08:53.968 --> 08:55.839
except the ones
doing the abusing.

08:57.624 --> 08:59.321
- It was dumb.

08:59.364 --> 09:02.542
These boys on the subway
wanted my MetroCard.

09:02.585 --> 09:05.109
I said no, so they
started wailing on me.

09:05.153 --> 09:08.417
- That used to happen
to me a lot.

09:08.460 --> 09:10.593
So it's just you, your mom,
and your sister at home?

09:10.637 --> 09:11.725
- Most of the time.

09:11.768 --> 09:14.771
- Except when Dwight
stays over.

09:14.815 --> 09:18.340
You and Dwight get along?

09:18.383 --> 09:20.516
- I don't like it
when he yells at my mom.

09:20.560 --> 09:21.865
- Was he yelling at her today?

09:21.909 --> 09:24.389
- Will!
- Dad.

09:26.522 --> 09:27.610
- How you doing, buddy?

09:27.654 --> 09:29.177
Marc Vargas,
with the one-one-seven.

09:29.220 --> 09:30.265
Let me take Will
off your hands.

09:30.308 --> 09:32.267
- Kat Tamin, SVU.
We're almost done.

09:32.310 --> 09:34.922
- I get it, but I don't want
my boy being dragged into this.

09:34.965 --> 09:37.315
Will, go play with your sister.

09:41.232 --> 09:42.756
[sighs]

09:42.799 --> 09:45.280
So I guess Dwight's
back in town?

09:45.323 --> 09:47.325
I'm not just saying this
'cause I'm her ex.

09:47.369 --> 09:49.545
The guy has
anger management issues.

09:49.589 --> 09:52.940
- Your son told me
that he got mugged.

09:52.983 --> 09:55.203
- I'll talk to him
and fill you in.

09:55.246 --> 09:57.988
I should've fought harder
for custody.

09:59.511 --> 10:01.339
Irena and Dwight...

10:01.383 --> 10:02.776
[sighs]

10:02.819 --> 10:05.169
Takes two to tango,
and they've tangoed for years.

10:07.345 --> 10:09.260
- A son with bruises,
a mother with a black eye,

10:09.304 --> 10:10.784
and the only one
accusing the boyfriend

10:10.827 --> 10:11.959
is the ex-husband.

10:12.002 --> 10:13.787
- Will and Irena are afraid.

10:13.830 --> 10:16.267
- Does--the boyfriend, Dwight,
does he have a record?

10:16.311 --> 10:17.921
- A lot of mis-ds
including assault.

10:17.965 --> 10:19.096
- On Irena?

10:19.140 --> 10:20.402
- Bar fight.
West Virginia.

10:20.445 --> 10:21.882
- That is no help.
- Hold up.

10:21.925 --> 10:24.667
The local precinct
responded three times

10:24.711 --> 10:27.148
to neighbor complaints
when Dwight was in town.

10:27.191 --> 10:28.671
Shouting, breaking glass.

10:28.715 --> 10:30.281
- And when the cops showed up?

10:30.325 --> 10:32.980
- Well, she stood by her man
but that's par for the course.

10:33.023 --> 10:34.677
- So she won't file
a complaint?

10:34.721 --> 10:36.505
- [sighs]

10:36.548 --> 10:38.376
- Can you get her to request
a restraining order?

10:38.420 --> 10:39.551
- I can try.
[phone vibrating]

10:39.595 --> 10:41.945
But she will be afraid,
rightly so,

10:41.989 --> 10:43.817
that Dwight will view that
as an escalation.

10:43.860 --> 10:44.905
- Dwight doesn't live here,
right?

10:44.948 --> 10:46.341
- No.

10:46.384 --> 10:47.951
- Best bet, find a way
to get him on the road.

10:47.995 --> 10:50.345
Carisi.

10:50.388 --> 10:53.783
- Dwight is staying
an extra day to care of me.

10:53.827 --> 10:55.437
He's out getting Aspirin now.

10:55.480 --> 10:58.135
- Okay.
I-I understand that, Irena.

10:58.179 --> 11:01.704
But--but it's not just you

11:01.748 --> 11:03.837
that I'm worried about.

11:03.880 --> 11:06.187
- My children?

11:06.230 --> 11:08.189
I take care of them.

11:08.232 --> 11:11.235
And Dwight would
never hurt LeAnn.

11:13.194 --> 11:14.978
- What about Will?

11:15.022 --> 11:18.329
- Of course not.
I-I meant to say that.

11:18.373 --> 11:20.418
I'm just still not all here.

11:20.462 --> 11:22.203
<i>[tense music]</i>

11:22.246 --> 11:24.553
In fact, the doctor wants me
to take it easy,

11:24.596 --> 11:26.990
and my ex is about
to bring the kids back so...

11:27.034 --> 11:28.383
- I understand but, you know,

11:28.426 --> 11:31.125
maybe, um,

11:31.168 --> 11:34.258
the kids could stay
with your ex-husband tonight.

11:35.390 --> 11:37.566
I think that would
be easier for you.

11:37.609 --> 11:40.743
- Marc's new wife,
she didn't love that idea.

11:40.787 --> 11:43.398
<i>♪</i>

11:43.441 --> 11:46.227
- Well, then--
- We're fine.

11:46.270 --> 11:49.273
We're all gonna be fine.

11:52.799 --> 11:54.757
- My dad was upset.

11:54.801 --> 11:56.150
So I ran to him.

11:56.193 --> 11:57.804
- You weren't afraid
of your dad?

11:57.847 --> 12:00.154
- No.

12:00.197 --> 12:02.156
- Not even when he put a knife
to your throat?

12:02.199 --> 12:05.420
- Daddy wouldn't hurt me.

12:05.463 --> 12:07.770
Why'd you have to shoot him,
Sergeant Tutuola?

12:07.814 --> 12:13.080
<i>♪</i>

12:13.123 --> 12:14.255
- Checking in.

12:14.298 --> 12:16.039
- Hey.
How'd it go?

12:16.083 --> 12:17.867
- Joelle claims she's worried
about Andre

12:17.911 --> 12:19.608
but then she made him testify.

12:19.651 --> 12:21.349
She's got her eyes
on the prize.

12:21.392 --> 12:23.438
- Fin, you and I both know

12:23.481 --> 12:26.702
that you did what you had
to do that night.

12:26.746 --> 12:28.269
Everything is being looked at

12:28.312 --> 12:30.140
through a different prism now.

12:30.184 --> 12:32.882
- It is what it is.

12:32.926 --> 12:35.145
- These lawsuits,
these depositions--

12:35.189 --> 12:37.974
don't underestimate
how painful

12:38.018 --> 12:42.022
and how exhausting they can be.

12:42.065 --> 12:44.459
You gotta take care
of yourself, Fin.

12:44.502 --> 12:46.548
There's more to life
than this job.

12:46.591 --> 12:47.636
Trust me.

12:47.679 --> 12:49.290
- You sound like Phoebe.

12:49.333 --> 12:50.857
- How's that going?

12:50.900 --> 12:53.598
- About the only good thing
to come out of this pandemic.

12:55.165 --> 12:56.210
- Hey, I just got an alert.

12:56.253 --> 12:58.560
Irena's building.

12:58.603 --> 13:00.605
- Okay, Kat.
You and I will go up.

13:00.649 --> 13:01.737
- I'll go.

13:01.781 --> 13:04.305
I mean, I'm still on the job,
right?

13:04.348 --> 13:07.743
<i>[tense dramatic music]</i>

13:07.787 --> 13:09.701
- Hey.
- Hey, Kat.

13:09.745 --> 13:11.268
EMTs just called it.

13:11.312 --> 13:13.183
- Is she gone?
- "She"?

13:13.227 --> 13:16.839
<i>♪</i>

13:16.883 --> 13:18.798
You mean he?

13:18.841 --> 13:19.842
- What happened?

13:19.886 --> 13:21.235
- He was in the tub

13:21.278 --> 13:23.715
with that hair dryer
still plugged into the wall.

13:23.759 --> 13:25.326
Full cardiac arrest.

13:25.369 --> 13:26.849
- Who called it in?

13:26.893 --> 13:28.198
- Dead guy's girlfriend.

13:28.242 --> 13:30.853
She and her daughter
are with the super's family.

13:30.897 --> 13:37.773
<i>♪</i>

13:43.605 --> 13:45.607
- So Irena's abusive boyfriend

13:45.650 --> 13:48.915
ends up electrocuted
by a hair dryer

13:48.958 --> 13:50.438
in the bath tub?

13:50.481 --> 13:52.570
Kicking it old school.

13:52.614 --> 13:54.485
- And the ME confirms cause.

13:54.529 --> 13:56.879
It was an old model
blow dryer.

13:56.923 --> 13:59.273
Pre-war building
with faulty wiring,

13:59.316 --> 14:00.883
manner not yet determined.

14:00.927 --> 14:01.884
- [groans]

14:01.928 --> 14:03.886
Do we think this was
an accident?

14:08.935 --> 14:11.894
Okay.
What did she say on the way in?

14:11.938 --> 14:14.244
- Only that her ex-husband,
the cop,

14:14.288 --> 14:16.029
told her to wait
for her lawyer.

14:16.072 --> 14:17.508
- Great.
The kids with her?

14:17.552 --> 14:19.467
- LeAnn was there.
Son was with the ex.

14:19.510 --> 14:22.557
- Come up with Kat.
Bring him here.

14:23.863 --> 14:25.821
- Hey.
Irena's lawyer is--

14:25.865 --> 14:28.041
- Tommy Calabrese.
Formerly with the PBA.

14:28.084 --> 14:30.391
DA's office here already?

14:30.434 --> 14:33.307
I hope this isn't
a rush to judgment.

14:33.350 --> 14:34.961
[door opens]

14:35.004 --> 14:37.485
So it's pretty clear that we're
looking at a tragic accident.

14:37.528 --> 14:39.313
- Okay.
We just--

14:39.356 --> 14:42.490
just need to hear from Irena.

14:42.533 --> 14:44.492
- That's right.
It was an accident.

14:44.535 --> 14:46.450
[door shuts]

14:46.494 --> 14:48.148
- Okay.

14:48.191 --> 14:49.540
[sighs]

14:49.584 --> 14:52.543
So, uh, Irena, we know

14:52.587 --> 14:54.850
that you called 911.
- Mm-hmm.

14:54.894 --> 14:56.373
- You found him?

14:56.417 --> 14:57.722
- Mm-hmm.

14:57.766 --> 15:00.029
Dwight had been
in the tub a while.

15:00.073 --> 15:01.509
LeAnn needed to pee.

15:01.552 --> 15:02.727
I knocked.

15:02.771 --> 15:05.992
There was no answer,
so I went in.

15:06.035 --> 15:08.472
- What did you see?

15:08.516 --> 15:10.474
- He--he was just lying there.

15:10.518 --> 15:12.520
Uh, I saw the hair dryer.

15:12.563 --> 15:14.130
It must have fallen in.

15:14.174 --> 15:16.132
- Fallen in from where?

15:16.176 --> 15:18.700
- It's usually on a shelf
above the sink.

15:18.743 --> 15:20.528
- Do you usually keep it
plugged in, turned on?

15:20.571 --> 15:22.356
- She told you what she saw.

15:22.399 --> 15:23.835
- Okay.

15:23.879 --> 15:26.664
Irena...

15:26.708 --> 15:28.405
and then what did you do next?

15:28.449 --> 15:30.712
- Uh...

15:30.755 --> 15:32.714
I didn't know what to do.

15:32.757 --> 15:34.237
Um, I was afraid to touch him.

15:34.281 --> 15:35.847
And I didn't want LeAnn to see

15:35.891 --> 15:38.633
so I closed the door
and called 911.

15:38.676 --> 15:40.026
- And what about Will?

15:40.069 --> 15:41.897
You told me yesterday
when we were talking

15:41.941 --> 15:45.248
that your ex-husband was
dropping off LeAnn and Will.

15:45.292 --> 15:48.382
<i>[somber music]</i>

15:48.425 --> 15:50.775
- Well, I, um...

15:50.819 --> 15:52.777
I told Marc
that you were nervous

15:52.821 --> 15:54.475
about Dwight staying with Will

15:54.518 --> 15:56.390
so he kept him
at his house overnight.

15:56.433 --> 16:03.005
<i>♪</i>

16:03.049 --> 16:04.659
[water running]

16:08.010 --> 16:11.100
- Mister?
When can I see my mom?

16:11.144 --> 16:13.494
- Soon.

16:13.537 --> 16:14.930
You, uh--
you doing okay in here?

16:14.974 --> 16:17.193
- I got this, Mr. Carisi.
- I'm hungry.

16:17.237 --> 16:20.066
- We can get you some, uh--
some pizza?

16:20.109 --> 16:21.589
- Can I get a hot dog?

16:21.632 --> 16:23.373
- Yeah, sure.
We could do that.

16:23.417 --> 16:24.505
How about two?

16:24.548 --> 16:25.810
- Mm-hmm.

16:25.854 --> 16:27.943
Will doesn't like hot dogs.

16:27.987 --> 16:29.945
Last night I asked him for one

16:29.989 --> 16:32.513
but he said they have
to kill cows to make them.

16:32.556 --> 16:33.993
- Oh.

16:34.036 --> 16:36.604
So, uh, your brother
made dinner last night?

16:36.647 --> 16:38.475
- Uh-huh.
Veggie burgers.

16:38.519 --> 16:39.999
Ugh.

16:40.042 --> 16:42.958
Right before Daddy
had his accident.

16:43.002 --> 16:45.265
<i>♪</i>

16:45.308 --> 16:47.789
- [sighs]

16:47.832 --> 16:49.660
- And you're sure
that she meant last night?

16:49.704 --> 16:52.620
- Yeah, pretty sure.
- Oh.

16:52.663 --> 16:53.838
- Can I take LeAnn home now?

16:53.882 --> 16:56.319
- We still have some things
to sort out.

16:56.363 --> 16:58.365
- Will.
Will!

16:58.408 --> 17:00.802
- Mom!
- What's he doing here?

17:00.845 --> 17:02.064
He doesn't know
anything about this.

17:02.108 --> 17:04.936
- Right.
Um...

17:04.980 --> 17:06.373
Just...

17:06.416 --> 17:08.201
He's gonna have
to tell us that.

17:08.244 --> 17:09.985
Let's go have a seat.

17:10.029 --> 17:12.814
- Officer Vargas,
I appreciate you coming in.

17:12.857 --> 17:14.468
Kat, take them
to the Interview Room.

17:14.511 --> 17:17.340
Fin, you have a minute?

17:17.384 --> 17:20.822
- Come on.
- This way.

17:20.865 --> 17:24.173
- My dad picked me
and LeAnn up.

17:24.217 --> 17:26.001
You were there.
You saw.

17:26.045 --> 17:28.003
- I did.

17:28.047 --> 17:29.396
And he took you back
to his house?

17:29.439 --> 17:31.006
- Both kids.

17:31.050 --> 17:32.268
My wife, Carmen,
was not too happy about it

17:32.312 --> 17:34.140
so I drove the girl
back to the apartment.

17:34.183 --> 17:36.359
- LeAnn but not Will?

17:36.403 --> 17:38.361
- I wanted to go with her.

17:38.405 --> 17:40.668
But Dad wouldn't let me.

17:40.711 --> 17:42.931
'Cause of Dwight.
- I get it.

17:42.974 --> 17:46.065
So you had dinner
with your step-mom?

17:48.719 --> 17:51.766
- Sergeant, what's this about?

17:51.809 --> 17:54.856
- You have veggie burgers?
- Yeah.

17:56.640 --> 17:57.989
How'd you know that?

17:58.033 --> 18:00.035
- Your little sister like 'em?

18:03.560 --> 18:05.214
- Will was with me.

18:05.258 --> 18:08.870
And we're done here.

18:08.913 --> 18:10.785
- Look, man, relax.
We're both cops here.

18:10.828 --> 18:12.047
You already knew
we were gonna check

18:12.091 --> 18:13.918
the traffic cams and your cell.

18:13.962 --> 18:15.920
So you might as well
just tell us right now.

18:15.964 --> 18:18.880
Did Irena call you
when she found Dwight?

18:20.534 --> 18:23.754
- [sighs]

18:23.798 --> 18:26.714
She was in a panic.
She needed advice.

18:26.757 --> 18:28.498
- And she needed you
to come get Will?

18:28.542 --> 18:30.152
- Dad.
- Shut up, son.

18:30.196 --> 18:33.068
This is how you treat
a brother officer?

18:33.112 --> 18:35.505
No wonder you got lawsuits
against you.

18:35.549 --> 18:37.246
Will, let's go.

18:37.290 --> 18:38.595
- No.
Dad!

18:38.639 --> 18:40.293
- Now.
- Dad, ow!

18:40.336 --> 18:41.337
- Will.
- Stop.

18:41.381 --> 18:42.860
- Shut up.
- Dad, stop!

18:44.166 --> 18:46.386
[shaky gasp]
I was there.

18:46.429 --> 18:50.085
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

18:50.129 --> 18:52.783
And I did it.

18:52.827 --> 18:56.396
<i>They were arguing.
Mom was crying.</i>

18:56.439 --> 18:58.833
He was gonna hurt her again.

18:58.876 --> 19:01.183
I know he was.
I wouldn't let that happen.

19:01.227 --> 19:03.881
- I said shut up.

19:05.622 --> 19:07.537
How dumb are you?

19:07.581 --> 19:13.326
<i>♪</i>

19:13.369 --> 19:15.763
You guys played me.

19:15.806 --> 19:18.766
I knew I should've
brought a lawyer.

19:18.809 --> 19:22.291
Not another word
till he gets one.

19:25.251 --> 19:26.991
- I was afraid of this.
- [sighs]

19:27.035 --> 19:29.516
Will has been a punching bag
his whole life.

19:29.559 --> 19:32.823
He finally hit back.

19:39.265 --> 19:41.180
- I told you
Will wasn't in the house.

19:41.223 --> 19:43.051
- We know you called Marc

19:43.094 --> 19:44.270
to get your son
out of the house

19:44.313 --> 19:45.662
before you called the police.

19:45.706 --> 19:47.316
- Irena's just been
through a trauma.

19:47.360 --> 19:49.318
She's confused.
- And we understand that.

19:49.362 --> 19:53.496
So...why don't, um,
Irena, let's just--

19:53.540 --> 19:54.802
[breathes deeply]

19:54.845 --> 19:56.717
Let's just take a breath
and start over, okay?

20:00.242 --> 20:03.158
Will was home
when Dwight died.

20:04.072 --> 20:05.900
- Okay.
Yes.

20:05.943 --> 20:08.250
- So were they fighting?

20:08.294 --> 20:10.339
- [scoffs]
Neighbors tell you that?

20:10.383 --> 20:12.080
Like Dwight says, they should
mind their own business.

20:12.123 --> 20:13.908
- So Will was defending you.

20:13.951 --> 20:15.214
- Is that what Will is saying?

20:15.257 --> 20:18.042
- I told you I walked in
and Dwight was dead.

20:18.086 --> 20:19.261
It must've been an accident.

20:19.305 --> 20:21.220
- Thing is,
Will told us he was there,

20:21.263 --> 20:22.656
that he threw the dryer
into the tub.

20:22.699 --> 20:24.353
- No, no.
He's trying to protect me--

20:24.397 --> 20:25.441
- Irena, you need
to stop talking now.

20:25.485 --> 20:26.399
- Protect you
from what, Irena?

20:26.442 --> 20:27.661
- Shush.
- Protect you from what?

20:27.704 --> 20:28.705
- Do you have a confession
from the boy?

20:28.749 --> 20:29.967
- Yes, and we need
corroboration.

20:30.011 --> 20:31.230
So Irena needs to tell us--

20:31.273 --> 20:33.144
- No, she doesn't!
Is she under arrest?

20:33.188 --> 20:34.276
- No, but if you
wanna help your son...

20:34.320 --> 20:35.625
- Then I'm taking her
and LeAnn home.

20:35.669 --> 20:37.018
- You need to do that.
- I need to talk to Will.

20:37.061 --> 20:38.237
Is he gonna be okay?
- You can talk to him later.

20:38.280 --> 20:39.716
We are going home.
[snaps]

20:39.760 --> 20:42.110
Now.

20:42.153 --> 20:43.633
- [breathing heavily]

20:43.677 --> 20:46.723
- [whispering]
Irena, listen to me.

20:46.767 --> 20:51.772
<i>♪</i>

20:51.815 --> 20:54.165
Thanks, Pippa.
Okay.

20:54.209 --> 20:56.951
Pippa Cox has agreed
to defend Will.

20:56.994 --> 20:58.605
She's been doing child
defense work since I don't--

20:58.648 --> 21:01.738
- Yeah, since her husband went
to prison for child porn?

21:03.087 --> 21:04.263
- She's a good lawyer.

21:04.306 --> 21:05.438
- Yeah, well,
Will's gonna need one.

21:05.481 --> 21:07.091
- Carisi, are you gonna
charge this kid?

21:07.135 --> 21:08.397
- I'm sorry.
Do I have a choice?

21:08.441 --> 21:10.269
He just confessed.
- He's 14.

21:10.312 --> 21:12.271
He was bullied by Dwight.
Self-defense maybe.

21:12.314 --> 21:14.011
- Not unless he was threatened
in the moment.

21:14.055 --> 21:15.448
And his mother's
gotta confirm that.

21:15.491 --> 21:17.014
- She's still saying
it was an accident.

21:17.058 --> 21:20.104
- And that is coming from her
ex-husband and her lawyer.

21:20.148 --> 21:21.454
And in case you
haven't noticed,

21:21.497 --> 21:23.978
Irena does what men in her life
tell her to do.

21:24.021 --> 21:25.284
- If you ask me, she did it

21:25.327 --> 21:27.111
and she's letting her son
take the fall.

21:27.155 --> 21:30.289
I'm due back in my deposition.

21:30.332 --> 21:32.160
- [huffs]
Listen, I--

21:32.203 --> 21:34.031
I don't wanna charge Will.

21:34.075 --> 21:35.250
But something's
gotta give here.

21:35.294 --> 21:36.599
- Then give us a warrant

21:36.643 --> 21:38.906
for the cell phone,
computer, devices.

21:38.949 --> 21:40.211
- Fine.
Not a problem.

21:40.255 --> 21:41.212
What about the forensics
in the bathroom?

21:41.256 --> 21:42.431
- Useless!

21:42.475 --> 21:43.737
Everybody's fingerprints
are everywhere.

21:43.780 --> 21:45.956
- And nobody is telling us
the truth.

21:46.000 --> 21:48.394
Except LeAnn.
- Who's six.

21:48.437 --> 21:50.134
We can only talk to her
with her mother in the room.

21:50.178 --> 21:51.701
- Well, please.
Let's try that.

21:51.745 --> 21:54.574
Because unless you get me
something exculpatory,

21:54.617 --> 21:56.793
right now, Will is gonna take
the whole weight.

21:56.837 --> 21:58.752
- [sighs]

21:58.795 --> 22:00.449
- The lawyer told me
you can go through our stuff

22:00.493 --> 22:01.537
but I can't talk to you.

22:01.581 --> 22:03.409
- Okay, so does Will
have a computer?

22:03.452 --> 22:04.801
- That's his study area.
His backpack.

22:04.845 --> 22:08.196
- Go ahead.
And we'll also need your cell.

22:10.894 --> 22:12.592
LeAnn...

22:12.635 --> 22:14.768
You know, why don't you show
Officer Tamin your bedroom?

22:14.811 --> 22:16.465
- No, I'm sorry.

22:16.509 --> 22:18.119
The lawyer told me not to leave
her alone with either of you.

22:18.162 --> 22:20.469
- Okay.
The three of you go then.

22:20.513 --> 22:23.559
I'll stay here and supervise.

22:25.605 --> 22:27.694
- So this is your room, LeAnn?

22:27.737 --> 22:29.391
It's nice.

22:29.435 --> 22:31.088
- Will has the top bunk.

22:31.132 --> 22:33.700
When Daddy's not here,
I get to sleep with my mom.

22:36.311 --> 22:37.965
Is Will gonna be okay?

22:38.008 --> 22:40.968
- I hope so.

22:41.011 --> 22:43.362
If I were to ask LeAnn
about what happened that night,

22:43.405 --> 22:45.276
you'd want her
to tell the truth, right?

22:45.320 --> 22:46.539
- Um, of course.

22:46.582 --> 22:48.497
- My mom says
to always tell the truth.

22:48.541 --> 22:52.022
- That's 'cause
she's a good mom.

22:52.066 --> 22:54.503
- You won't get mad if I say
what happened to Daddy?

22:54.547 --> 22:56.331
- No, no, no.
Daddy's in heaven.

22:56.375 --> 22:57.811
Like we talked about.

22:57.854 --> 23:00.553
- That's right.
God's not mad at him,

23:00.596 --> 23:04.208
even though he was yelling.

23:04.252 --> 23:05.645
- Yelling at who?

23:05.688 --> 23:07.081
- The lawyer said
we shouldn't--

23:07.124 --> 23:08.735
- I remember.

23:08.778 --> 23:11.390
You said not to tell anyone,
Mommy.

23:11.433 --> 23:13.827
But he was yelling at you
and Will in the bathroom,

23:13.870 --> 23:16.395
right before
he had his accident.

23:16.438 --> 23:19.354
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

23:19.398 --> 23:24.054
<i>♪</i>

23:24.098 --> 23:25.186
<i>[knock at door]</i>

23:25.229 --> 23:28.232
[door opening]

23:28.276 --> 23:30.713
- Excuse me, Mr. Carisi?

23:30.757 --> 23:33.412
They said you're the lawyer
on Dwight Wagner's case?

23:33.455 --> 23:35.936
- Yes.
How can I help you?

23:35.979 --> 23:38.417
- I'm Sherry, his wife.

23:39.679 --> 23:41.376
Drove straight up
from Wayne county

23:41.420 --> 23:44.640
hoping someone would tell me
who murdered him.

23:44.684 --> 23:46.903
- Um...we're--
please, take a seat.

23:46.947 --> 23:49.210
We're still--

23:49.253 --> 23:52.909
we're still piecing that
together, ma'am.

23:52.953 --> 23:55.172
- I 't know what they've
been saying about him.

23:55.216 --> 23:58.306
But he was a good man.

23:59.394 --> 24:00.830
This baby...
[sniffles]

24:00.874 --> 24:03.485
Will never get
to meet his daddy.

24:03.529 --> 24:06.183
[phone vibrating]

24:06.227 --> 24:08.621
- Sorry.
Excuse me.

24:09.970 --> 24:12.407
Rollins.

24:12.451 --> 24:14.975
Okay.
Slow down.

24:18.500 --> 24:20.981
- It's inadmissible.
LeAnn's six.

24:21.024 --> 24:23.070
She doesn't know the difference
between truth and make believe.

24:23.113 --> 24:25.376
- Well, she knew her mother
told her to lie.

24:25.420 --> 24:26.595
- I didn't want them
to put Will in jail.

24:26.639 --> 24:28.467
- Irena, were you
in the bathroom

24:28.510 --> 24:29.772
with Will and Dwight?

24:29.816 --> 24:31.513
- You still have a confession
from the boy?

24:31.557 --> 24:33.080
He hasn't recanted?

24:33.123 --> 24:34.647
Then what are we doing here?

24:34.690 --> 24:38.085
- Will's story and LeAnn's
story don't match up.

24:38.128 --> 24:40.827
We need Irena to tell us
what actually happened.

24:40.870 --> 24:42.045
- The kid did it.

24:42.089 --> 24:43.569
Or it was an accident.

24:43.612 --> 24:45.484
And forgive me for saying this,

24:45.527 --> 24:48.138
but we're all better off
now that Dwight is gone.

24:48.182 --> 24:49.575
- All, huh?

24:49.618 --> 24:52.142
Does that include
his grieving, pregnant widow

24:52.186 --> 24:53.187
in West Virginia?

24:53.230 --> 24:54.797
<i>[tense music]</i>

24:54.841 --> 24:56.320
- Sherry?

24:56.364 --> 24:58.322
Dwight told me
they broke up years ago.

24:58.366 --> 24:59.628
- Huh.
Well, sorry.

24:59.672 --> 25:01.935
I thought you must have known.

25:01.978 --> 25:05.460
- Guess I do now.

25:05.504 --> 25:07.331
Well, whatever she's saying,

25:07.375 --> 25:08.942
it's common law at most.

25:08.985 --> 25:11.466
Dwight would never commit--
- Irena!

25:11.510 --> 25:14.077
Irena, Dwight was a liar.

25:14.121 --> 25:16.471
He lied to you.

25:16.515 --> 25:18.168
He abused you.

25:18.212 --> 25:20.649
He abused your son!

25:20.693 --> 25:23.826
I understand that
you were scared of him.

25:23.870 --> 25:27.090
So if there's anything--
- Enough, Captain!

25:27.134 --> 25:29.484
All right, there's no
mitigating circumstances

25:29.528 --> 25:30.746
because there's nothing
to mitigate.

25:30.790 --> 25:31.878
- Is that right, Irena?

25:31.921 --> 25:34.141
- Or did Mr. Calabrese
convince you

25:34.184 --> 25:35.708
to let your son do the time?

25:35.751 --> 25:37.710
- No, no, he won't go to jail.
He's 14.

25:37.753 --> 25:39.363
- Irena--
- Hold on.

25:39.407 --> 25:42.105
Is--is that what you told her?
Is that why she's not talking?

25:42.149 --> 25:43.367
You're forcing my hand.

25:43.411 --> 25:44.455
- Wait, what does he mean?

25:44.499 --> 25:46.109
- He's bluffing.
Don't worry.

25:46.153 --> 25:49.286
- All right.

25:49.330 --> 25:51.811
You have left me
no other choice.

25:51.854 --> 25:54.944
I will be charging Will
as an adult.

25:54.988 --> 26:01.908
<i>♪</i>

26:09.306 --> 26:10.786
- He's barely 14.

26:10.830 --> 26:12.048
You're gonna charge him
as an adult?

26:12.092 --> 26:14.094
This was clearly self-defense.

26:14.137 --> 26:17.445
- Electrocuting a naked man
in a bathtub?

26:17.488 --> 26:21.275
Dwight was no saint but
I don't see imminent danger.

26:21.318 --> 26:24.626
But if Will tells me what
really happened that night,

26:24.670 --> 26:25.932
I would be more than happy

26:25.975 --> 26:27.498
to redirect this
to juvenile court.

26:27.542 --> 26:29.892
- Where he can still be
locked up till he's 18?

26:29.936 --> 26:32.286
Dwight was terrorizing Will
that night.

26:32.329 --> 26:34.462
- Okay.
Let's say that's true.

26:34.505 --> 26:35.898
It's a small apartment.

26:35.942 --> 26:37.421
Your mother must have
heard something.

26:37.465 --> 26:38.684
- No.

26:38.727 --> 26:40.163
It wasn't "loud" loud.

26:40.207 --> 26:42.513
- Will, your sister
says it was.

26:42.557 --> 26:45.865
She said all three of you
were in the bathroom arguing.

26:45.908 --> 26:49.042
- LeAnn's a little girl.
She gets days confused.

26:50.304 --> 26:51.784
- Will, if your mom
was there with you,

26:51.827 --> 26:52.785
it's okay to say that.

26:52.828 --> 26:54.090
- My mom wasn't there.

26:54.134 --> 26:55.657
I swear.

26:55.701 --> 26:58.181
- Oh--okay.

26:58.225 --> 27:01.315
How about I give
you two the room?

27:02.925 --> 27:05.275
Will...

27:05.319 --> 27:07.713
I know you're worried
about your mom.

27:07.756 --> 27:10.280
But sooner or later,
the truth is going to come out.

27:10.324 --> 27:11.847
This is not
your responsibility.

27:11.891 --> 27:12.935
You're just a kid.

27:12.979 --> 27:15.634
- My mom wasn't there.
Just me.

27:15.677 --> 27:19.246
- [sighs]

27:19.289 --> 27:22.031
- LeAnn needed
to use the bathroom.

27:23.076 --> 27:25.644
I went in to tell Dwight.

27:25.687 --> 27:28.298
He told me to shut up.

27:28.342 --> 27:31.824
He said she could use
the kitchen sink.

27:31.867 --> 27:34.217
He said he'd deal
with me and my mom later.

27:34.261 --> 27:37.743
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

27:37.786 --> 27:39.962
<i>♪</i>

27:40.006 --> 27:42.878
I saw the hair dryer.

27:44.097 --> 27:46.055
I saw him in the tub.

27:46.099 --> 27:48.362
I guess I just snapped.

27:51.582 --> 27:53.802
- He was in the tub, Will?

27:53.846 --> 27:55.978
- Yeah, I just told you.

27:56.022 --> 27:58.241
- [whispers]
Okay.

27:58.285 --> 28:00.069
[talking]
He sticks to that story,

28:00.113 --> 28:01.897
there goes self-defense.

28:01.941 --> 28:08.382
<i>♪</i>

28:08.425 --> 28:09.905
[sighs]

28:13.822 --> 28:16.695
- The victim, Dwight Wagner,
died of cardiac arrest

28:16.738 --> 28:19.088
due to electrocution
caused by a hair dryer

28:19.132 --> 28:20.350
in his bathtub.

28:20.394 --> 28:22.657
- In your experience,
is there any way

28:22.701 --> 28:25.355
that his death
could've been an accident?

28:25.399 --> 28:28.315
- You mean was he blow-drying
his hair while taking a bath?

28:28.358 --> 28:30.012
That would be highly unlikely

28:30.056 --> 28:32.711
given the room geography
and tub position.

28:32.754 --> 28:34.495
- Geography and position.

28:34.538 --> 28:36.976
- His head was
at the farthest end of the tub,

28:37.019 --> 28:39.065
the dryer at his feet,

28:39.108 --> 28:40.719
and the outlet
four feet from there.

28:40.762 --> 28:43.504
- Was there any chance
that he was standing up?

28:43.547 --> 28:45.985
- There are no signs of
bruising or the body falling.

28:46.028 --> 28:48.117
- So he was lying in the tub

28:48.161 --> 28:49.728
when he was electrocuted?

28:49.771 --> 28:51.773
- In my opinion, yes.

28:51.817 --> 28:53.732
- Thank you, doctor.

28:53.775 --> 28:57.213
- Dr. Truman,
you weren't in the bathroom

28:57.257 --> 28:58.824
at the time of the fatal
incident, were you?

28:58.867 --> 29:00.521
- Me?
No, of course not.

29:00.564 --> 29:02.392
- The prosecutor wants
this jury to believe

29:02.436 --> 29:04.786
that because Mr. Wagner
was in the tub,

29:04.830 --> 29:06.614
Will was not in any danger.

29:06.657 --> 29:10.400
In your opinion,
could a 6'3", 180 pound man

29:10.444 --> 29:12.141
seem threatening
to a 14-year-old boy?

29:12.185 --> 29:13.490
- Objection.
Speculation.

29:13.534 --> 29:14.753
- I'll rephrase.

29:14.796 --> 29:17.886
You can't know if Will
did feel threatened.

29:17.930 --> 29:19.148
- I can't know what he felt.

29:19.192 --> 29:21.803
I only know the physical
and forensic reality

29:21.847 --> 29:23.979
of a dead man in a tub.

29:27.853 --> 29:29.985
- Irena called, said there
had been an accident,

29:30.029 --> 29:31.421
that Dwight was dead,

29:31.465 --> 29:33.423
that I had to get Will
out of the house.

29:33.467 --> 29:36.687
- And, um, what did you
take that to mean?

29:39.038 --> 29:41.170
- That Will was
somehow involved.

29:41.214 --> 29:43.216
- You assumed

29:43.259 --> 29:45.958
that Will had killed Dwight?
- Yes.

29:46.001 --> 29:48.003
But I knew it was self-defense.

29:48.047 --> 29:49.962
- But you didn't tell that
to the cops.

29:50.005 --> 29:51.267
- No.

29:51.311 --> 29:53.356
- In fact, didn't you drive
to the apartment

29:53.400 --> 29:54.923
and get Will out of there?

29:54.967 --> 29:56.577
And then tell the police

29:56.620 --> 29:58.579
that Will wasn't there
when Dwight was killed?

29:58.622 --> 30:01.190
- I...didn't know
what happened.

30:01.234 --> 30:03.192
I-I was just worried
about my son.

30:03.236 --> 30:05.934
- Mr. Vargas,
as a police officer,

30:05.978 --> 30:07.631
if somebody lies to you

30:07.675 --> 30:10.069
instead of claiming
self-defense,

30:10.112 --> 30:12.375
what does that tell you?

30:14.813 --> 30:17.076
- What do you want me to say?

30:19.295 --> 30:21.036
- Nothing further.

30:23.082 --> 30:25.258
- Officer Vargas,

30:25.301 --> 30:28.174
did you know your son had been
bullied by Dwight Wagner?

30:29.131 --> 30:31.873
- I was aware.

30:31.917 --> 30:33.875
I should have
intervened sooner.

30:33.919 --> 30:35.442
I blame myself.

30:35.485 --> 30:37.923
- Do you believe
Will was afraid of Dwight?

30:37.966 --> 30:40.055
- Terrified.
- Afraid for his life?

30:40.099 --> 30:42.666
- Objection.
Again, calls for speculation.

30:42.710 --> 30:44.494
- Sustained.

30:44.538 --> 30:46.801
- Mr. Vargas,

30:46.845 --> 30:49.760
do you think your son
is capable of murder?

30:51.893 --> 30:54.461
- No.

30:54.504 --> 30:56.506
He's a good kid.

30:56.550 --> 30:58.639
He'd never do anything
to harm another human being

30:58.682 --> 31:01.381
unless he was
absolutely forced to.

31:01.424 --> 31:03.862
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

31:03.905 --> 31:05.080
- Thank you.

31:05.124 --> 31:07.517
[footsteps]

31:09.128 --> 31:10.477
[door creaks]

31:10.520 --> 31:12.522
- Irena.

31:12.566 --> 31:14.698
There you are.
[door closes]

31:14.742 --> 31:16.918
- Do you know when
they'll call me to testify?

31:16.962 --> 31:18.093
It's been hours.

31:18.137 --> 31:19.921
- I-I don't know.

31:19.965 --> 31:22.358
But, um...

31:22.402 --> 31:25.796
But your ex-husband
just got off the stand.

31:25.840 --> 31:29.365
- Did he blame me?

31:29.409 --> 31:32.151
The whole time we were married,

31:32.194 --> 31:34.153
any time anything went wrong,

31:34.196 --> 31:35.894
it was always my fault.

31:35.937 --> 31:37.373
[breathing shakily]

31:37.417 --> 31:40.289
If--if I--
if I tried to explain,

31:40.333 --> 31:43.292
it didn't matter.

31:43.336 --> 31:45.251
He never listened to me.

31:45.294 --> 31:48.297
<i>♪</i>

31:48.341 --> 31:51.083
He was right to blame me.

31:51.126 --> 31:53.607
I should have known better.

31:53.650 --> 31:56.392
- [sighs]
Irena...

31:56.436 --> 31:58.307
- I grew up in a house

31:58.351 --> 32:01.571
where someone got beaten
every single day.

32:01.615 --> 32:05.053
I swore I wouldn't
let that happen to my kids.

32:05.097 --> 32:10.885
<i>♪</i>

32:10.929 --> 32:12.582
<i>- I don't know
why Leon thought that.</i>

32:12.626 --> 32:14.410
<i>I was not involved
with Joelle.</i>

32:14.454 --> 32:15.846
<i>My only concern was Andre,</i>

32:15.890 --> 32:18.414
a young boy trying
to protect his mom.

32:18.458 --> 32:20.939
- So on the night
of Leon's murder--

32:20.982 --> 32:23.071
I'm sorry, death--

32:23.115 --> 32:24.507
you came to his home.

32:24.551 --> 32:26.727
You inserted yourself
in their domestic situation.

32:26.770 --> 32:30.165
Andre, frightened that you were
going to hurt his father,

32:30.209 --> 32:31.819
rushed to his dad's side,
right?

32:31.862 --> 32:33.125
- No.

32:33.168 --> 32:35.301
Leon called him
to use him as a shield.

32:35.344 --> 32:38.652
- Leon would've
never hurt Andre.

32:38.695 --> 32:39.870
He--he loved him.

32:39.914 --> 32:41.437
- It doesn't matter.

32:41.481 --> 32:43.439
I've seen this
so many times before.

32:43.483 --> 32:45.050
A man in that state,

32:45.093 --> 32:47.095
he'll take his wife
and his kid down.

32:47.139 --> 32:50.359
If he can't have you,
nobody can.

32:50.403 --> 32:52.057
There's no way he was gonna let

32:52.100 --> 32:54.711
the two of you walk
out of there.

32:57.540 --> 33:00.195
- Will asked Dwight
to get out of the bathroom.

33:00.239 --> 33:02.023
I heard Dwight
calling Will names

33:02.067 --> 33:03.982
and threatening him.

33:04.025 --> 33:05.113
- How so?

33:05.157 --> 33:06.941
- Saying Will was gonna pay,

33:06.985 --> 33:08.290
that he'd had enough.

33:08.334 --> 33:10.292
I could hear splashing,

33:10.336 --> 33:12.468
Will saying, "Stay away."

33:12.512 --> 33:14.253
- What did you think
was happening?

33:14.296 --> 33:16.820
- I was sure Dwight was getting
out of the tub to attack Will.

33:16.864 --> 33:18.822
- But you didn't go in,
try to stop it?

33:18.866 --> 33:20.085
- By the time
I opened the door,

33:20.128 --> 33:21.695
it was too late.

33:21.738 --> 33:22.913
Dwight was dead.

33:22.957 --> 33:24.350
- Can you tell the jury why

33:24.393 --> 33:27.831
you didn't call 911
right away?

33:27.875 --> 33:30.008
- I was sure it was
self-defense

33:30.051 --> 33:33.054
but I was afraid of...

33:33.098 --> 33:35.056
of this.

33:35.100 --> 33:37.928
I should have told the truth
from the beginning.

33:37.972 --> 33:40.235
I'm sorry.

33:46.459 --> 33:49.940
- Ms. Nowak, when you went
into the bathroom,

33:49.984 --> 33:51.333
what did you see?

33:51.377 --> 33:53.161
- Dwight was in the tub, dead.

33:53.205 --> 33:54.554
Will was in shock.

33:54.597 --> 33:56.730
- Did you see the hair dryer?

33:56.773 --> 33:58.384
- I saw the cord.

33:58.427 --> 34:01.169
It was plugged in and off
the shelf I keep it on.

34:01.213 --> 34:04.346
- Okay, so Will had to reach
for the hair dryer.

34:04.390 --> 34:06.000
He had to take it
off the shelf.

34:06.044 --> 34:07.219
He had to unwind the cord.

34:07.262 --> 34:09.047
And he had to plug it in,
right?

34:09.090 --> 34:10.396
- Yes.

34:10.439 --> 34:12.876
- And all of that
would've taken time--

34:12.920 --> 34:14.269
more than enough time

34:14.313 --> 34:15.792
for Dwight to get out
of the tub

34:15.836 --> 34:17.359
and attack Will

34:17.403 --> 34:19.361
if that's really what
Dwight intended to do.

34:19.405 --> 34:21.102
But there was no sign
of a struggle.

34:21.146 --> 34:23.713
Dwight was lying, submerged,

34:23.757 --> 34:25.150
his head on the far side
of the tub.

34:25.193 --> 34:26.890
- I don't remember.

34:26.934 --> 34:28.805
- Do you remember thinking that
your son had murdered Dwight?

34:28.849 --> 34:30.155
- Objection!

34:30.198 --> 34:31.417
- I'll allow it.

34:31.460 --> 34:33.375
You may answer the question,
Ms. Nowak.

34:33.419 --> 34:35.073
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

34:35.116 --> 34:37.118
- Oh, are you looking
at--at your lawyer?

34:37.162 --> 34:39.468
Maybe--maybe look at your son.

34:39.512 --> 34:45.257
<i>♪</i>

34:45.300 --> 34:48.086
- I didn't know what to think.
I was trying to protect him.

34:48.129 --> 34:49.478
- Well, from what?

34:49.522 --> 34:50.610
From being charged with murder?

34:50.653 --> 34:51.698
- My son is innocent.

34:51.741 --> 34:52.786
He shouldn't even
be sitting there.

34:52.829 --> 34:55.267
- Mom, stop!

34:55.310 --> 34:56.268
- [whispers]
Sit down.

34:56.311 --> 34:57.573
- He didn't kill Dwight.

34:57.617 --> 34:59.184
- Well, how do you know that,
Ms. Nowak?

34:59.227 --> 35:01.403
- Because I did!

35:01.447 --> 35:08.584
<i>♪</i>

35:23.077 --> 35:25.035
- Irena breaks down
on the stand.

35:25.079 --> 35:26.428
Is she trying
to cause a mistrial?

35:26.472 --> 35:27.560
- I don't think that
that's what's going on here.

35:27.603 --> 35:28.648
- Maybe Pippa Cox
coached her into it.

35:28.691 --> 35:29.823
- I was watching Pippa.

35:29.866 --> 35:31.477
She was more shocked
than you are.

35:31.520 --> 35:34.654
- So Will's been covering
for her from the start, huh?

35:34.697 --> 35:36.308
- He has been trying

35:36.351 --> 35:38.788
to protect his mother
his entire life.

35:38.832 --> 35:40.486
First from the ex-husband.

35:40.529 --> 35:41.661
Then from Dwight.

35:41.704 --> 35:43.402
And now...

35:43.445 --> 35:46.144
now from you.

35:50.583 --> 35:53.629
- My client was
in a fragile state of mind.

35:53.673 --> 35:56.502
The stress of seeing her son
at the defense table--

35:56.545 --> 35:58.678
- Are you saying that she
perjured herself on the stand?

35:58.721 --> 35:59.766
- No, I am not saying that.

35:59.809 --> 36:01.985
- How about you let Irena

36:02.029 --> 36:05.511
tell us what happened
that night.

36:05.554 --> 36:08.514
<i>[dramatic muisc]</i>

36:08.557 --> 36:11.865
<i>♪</i>

36:11.908 --> 36:15.042
- LeAnn needed
to use the bathroom.

36:15.085 --> 36:17.000
Will went in first.

36:17.044 --> 36:18.480
Dwight started yelling.

36:18.524 --> 36:19.699
- Okay.
What did you see?

36:19.742 --> 36:21.483
- Dwight in the tub.

36:21.527 --> 36:23.703
My son holding the hair dryer.

36:23.746 --> 36:25.574
And Dwight--
Dwight was taunting him,

36:25.618 --> 36:27.881
saying he didn't have
the nerve to drop it.

36:27.924 --> 36:29.187
That when he finished his bath,

36:29.230 --> 36:30.797
he'd take care of me and Will,

36:30.840 --> 36:32.799
that we'd be sorry.

36:32.842 --> 36:35.715
- Okay, Irena.

36:35.758 --> 36:39.936
And what happened next?

36:40.633 --> 36:43.549
- Will said that he'd never
let anyone hurt me again,

36:43.592 --> 36:46.334
that he'd had enough,

36:46.378 --> 36:48.989
that he was gonna
take care of the family.

36:51.687 --> 36:54.255
I couldn't let him do it.

36:54.299 --> 36:56.257
So I did.

36:56.301 --> 36:58.738
<i>♪</i>

36:58.781 --> 37:01.610
- Did you think,
in that moment,

37:01.654 --> 37:05.440
that Dwight was
about to hurt you or your son?

37:07.050 --> 37:09.052
- I thought in that moment

37:09.096 --> 37:11.664
that if I waited for Dwight
to get out of the tub,

37:11.707 --> 37:13.187
it would be too late.

37:13.231 --> 37:15.581
- Clearly self-defense.

37:15.624 --> 37:16.930
We're not taking a plea.

37:16.973 --> 37:18.148
And if you take it to trial,

37:18.192 --> 37:19.672
we will put Will on the stand,

37:19.715 --> 37:20.586
and he will swear
that he did it.

37:20.629 --> 37:21.978
- No.

37:22.022 --> 37:24.285
No, no, he won't.
Not after I talk to him.

37:24.329 --> 37:25.678
- Irena, they don't
have a case.

37:25.721 --> 37:26.592
We're good.
And we're going now.

37:26.635 --> 37:27.810
- No, no.

37:27.854 --> 37:30.291
- [sighs]
Jesus, how stupid are you?

37:30.335 --> 37:32.250
They are handing
you and your son

37:32.293 --> 37:33.773
a Get Out of Jail Free card.

37:33.816 --> 37:35.035
Just take it and thank me.

37:35.078 --> 37:36.819
- Do you always talk
to women like that?

37:36.863 --> 37:38.778
- Excuse me, "Captain."

37:38.821 --> 37:40.562
This is between
my client and I.

37:40.606 --> 37:42.912
- What if I don't want
to be your client anymore?

37:42.956 --> 37:43.957
Can I fire him?

37:44.000 --> 37:44.914
- Yes!
- Yes, you can.

37:44.958 --> 37:46.176
- I need the room.

37:46.220 --> 37:47.308
I need to tell Irena
what's good for her.

37:47.352 --> 37:49.528
- No, no.
I am done listening to you.

37:49.571 --> 37:50.833
I can't take it anymore.

37:50.877 --> 37:52.574
- You are making a big mistake.

37:52.618 --> 37:53.967
- Get out!

37:54.010 --> 37:56.535
Get out!
Get out now!

37:56.578 --> 37:58.276
- You heard her.

37:58.319 --> 38:01.888
Counselor.

38:01.931 --> 38:09.069
<i>♪</i>

38:15.031 --> 38:16.337
- Before you say another word,
Irena,

38:16.381 --> 38:18.513
we need to get you
a new lawyer.

38:18.557 --> 38:20.776
- Mm-hmm.

38:20.820 --> 38:23.475
<i>♪</i>

38:23.518 --> 38:25.172
<i>That night,</i>

38:25.215 --> 38:28.828
I saw my son about to give up
his life for me.

38:28.871 --> 38:31.134
I couldn't let that happen.

38:31.178 --> 38:33.572
I took the dryer out
of his hand.

38:33.615 --> 38:36.009
Dwight had that--that look,

38:36.052 --> 38:37.967
and I knew
if I didn't stop him,

38:38.011 --> 38:40.840
there was gonna be hell to pay.

38:40.883 --> 38:42.537
I threw the dryer in.

38:42.581 --> 38:45.366
My son was just trying
to protect me.

38:45.410 --> 38:48.369
I'm the one who
should've been protecting him.

38:49.805 --> 38:51.764
- Counselor?

38:51.807 --> 38:54.419
- Your Honor, given
the traumatic circumstances,

38:54.462 --> 38:56.551
the state has no interest
in pursuing charges

38:56.595 --> 38:58.118
against Will Vargas,

38:58.161 --> 39:00.642
and we will accept
a guilty plea

39:00.686 --> 39:02.818
of criminally negligent
homicide from Ms. Nowak.

39:02.862 --> 39:05.691
- And how do you plead,
Ms. Nowak?

39:05.734 --> 39:07.562
- I'm guilty, Your Honor.

39:07.606 --> 39:09.390
<i>♪</i>

39:09.434 --> 39:11.349
- Having reviewed
all of the evidence,

39:11.392 --> 39:13.655
I accept the guilty verdict,

39:13.699 --> 39:16.005
and sentence Ms. Nowak
to a year in prison

39:16.049 --> 39:18.268
on the condition
that she and her family

39:18.312 --> 39:19.705
start getting
psychological help.

39:19.748 --> 39:21.054
- A year?

39:21.097 --> 39:23.752
A year?
That's all?

39:23.796 --> 39:25.058
- Ma'am, calm down please.

39:25.101 --> 39:27.234
- What?
She killed him.

39:27.277 --> 39:29.671
She killed the father
of my baby.

39:29.715 --> 39:31.412
- Officers, remove her please,
gently.

39:31.456 --> 39:32.979
- You killed him.
You killed my Dwight.

39:33.022 --> 39:34.328
You killed my husband!

39:34.372 --> 39:36.330
[thudding]
No, no!

39:36.374 --> 39:39.768
<i>[dramatic music intensifies]</i>

39:39.812 --> 39:46.732
<i>♪</i>

39:46.775 --> 39:50.083
- The city settled with Joelle
for 2 million.

39:50.126 --> 39:51.563
Seriously.

39:51.606 --> 39:54.261
- The attorney said
something about "optics."

39:54.304 --> 39:55.784
- Leon had a knife
to his son's throat.

39:55.828 --> 39:57.395
It was a good shooting.

39:57.438 --> 39:59.092
- Look, if I could do it
all over again,

39:59.135 --> 40:00.920
the minute Leon
violated his parole,

40:00.963 --> 40:02.530
I would have turned him in.

40:02.574 --> 40:04.010
- Hindsight's 20/20, Fin.

40:04.053 --> 40:05.794
- It used to be so simple,
you know?

40:05.838 --> 40:07.405
Just take down the bad guys.

40:07.448 --> 40:08.928
Now the lines are blurred,

40:08.971 --> 40:10.930
and half the city looking at us
like we're the bad guys.

40:10.973 --> 40:12.932
- It was an impossible summer.

40:12.975 --> 40:14.412
Things are gonna calm down.

40:14.455 --> 40:16.152
- Yeah.
I don't see that happening.

40:16.196 --> 40:17.806
The way that NYPD
handled the demonstrators...

40:17.850 --> 40:19.199
- We were under attack.

40:19.242 --> 40:20.461
What do you want us to do?
Sit there and take it?

40:20.505 --> 40:22.245
- We're supposed
to deescalate.

40:22.289 --> 40:24.422
We're supposed to be aware
of our bias, not over-react.

40:24.465 --> 40:26.685
- Like shoot a man
in front of his son?

40:26.728 --> 40:28.861
<i>[somber music]</i>

40:28.904 --> 40:31.820
- Fin...

40:31.864 --> 40:33.300
- Look, growing up in the hood,

40:33.343 --> 40:36.477
the way the cops treated us,
I never trusted 'em.

40:36.521 --> 40:38.827
That's why I joined the force:

40:38.871 --> 40:40.394
to try to make a change.

40:40.438 --> 40:43.310
Then I worked my way over
to SVU

40:43.353 --> 40:44.703
'cause there's no gray area

40:44.746 --> 40:47.357
when you're taking out
rapists and pedophiles.

40:47.401 --> 40:49.969
The last thing I wanted to be

40:50.012 --> 40:53.842
is another trigger-happy cop
that kills a Black man.

40:53.886 --> 40:56.845
And here I am.

40:56.889 --> 41:04.026
<i>♪</i>

41:14.559 --> 41:17.518
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

41:17.562 --> 41:24.482
<i>♪</i>

41:43.762 --> 41:46.721
[wolf howls]
